bscui

Produce interactive SVG figures with selectable and clickable user interface elements. These figures can be integrated in markdown documents or in shiny applications reacting to events triggered on them. Features also include moving, zoom in/out and export in SVG or PNG formats.

Installation

Dependencies

The following R packages available on CRAN are required:

  • htmlwidgets: HTML Widgets for R

And those are suggested:

  • knitr: A General-Purpose Package for Dynamic Report Generation in R
  • rmarkdown: Dynamic Documents for R
  • xml2: Parse XML
  • dplyr: A Grammar of Data Manipulation
  • readr: Read Rectangular Text Data
  • stringr: Simple, Consistent Wrappers for Common String Operations
  • glue: Interpreted String Literals
  • shiny: Web Application Framework for R
